#compdef go-cover-treemap
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# go-cover-treemap — generate heat treemaps from Go cover profiles as SVG
#                    (Go, 594★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/nikolaydubina/go-cover-treemap
# author : Nikolay Dubina (nikolaydubina) — author of the broader
#          `nikolaydubina/treemap` Go library that underlies this CLI
#          plus its sibling `go-binsize-treemap` and the `go-cover-
#          treemap`-related set of code-visualization tools
# license: MIT
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from main.go
# on the nikolaydubina/go-cover-treemap tip — Go stdlib `flag.StringVar`
# / `flag.Float64Var` / `flag.BoolVar` registrations parsed exactly as
# declared.
#
# Direct deps from go.mod (selected):
#   github.com/nikolaydubina/treemap  v1.2.5  (Nikolay's own pure-Go
#                                              treemap layout library
#                                              with SVG renderer that
#                                              emits SVG markup
#                                              directly via Go text
#                                              templates — the
#                                              minimalist pure-Go
#                                              answer to "I want SVG
#                                              output without dragging
#                                              in ajstarks/svgo or
#                                              srwiley/oksvg")
#   github.com/lucasb-eyer/go-colorful  v1.3.0 (Lucas Beyer's go-colorful
#                                               — IETF / sRGB / Lab /
#                                               HSL / Hex color space
#                                               conversions; used for
#                                               heat-map color gradients)
#   golang.org/x/tools/cover                   (Go stdlib-adjacent
#                                               coverage profile parser
#                                               from x/tools)
#
# go-cover-treemap takes a Go coverage profile (from `go test
# -coverprofile cover.out ./...`) and renders it as an SVG heat
# treemap: each rectangle is a file or directory, sized by statement
# count (or line count with `-statements=false`), colored by coverage
# percentage.  Pipe-friendly: `go-cover-treemap -coverprofile cover.out
# > out.svg`.  The sibling `go-binsize-treemap` does the same for
# binary size output from `go tool nm`.  Both ship as composable
# Unix-style filters that emit SVG to stdout.
#
# === AXIS 179 CONTINUES — pure-language SVG renderers/generators ========
# Axis position: Go=234 continues Axis 179 (slot 2/0/0).  Where the Rust
# opener (`mmdr`) anchored on `resvg`+`usvg` for SVG RENDERING (parsing
# + rasterizing existing SVG to PNG), the Go ecosystem has a different
# canonical mode: SVG GENERATION via libraries like `ajstarks/svgo`
# (the canonical pure-Go SVG writer) and Nikolay Dubina's own
# `nikolaydubina/treemap` (data → SVG via text templates).  `srwiley/
# oksvg` + `srwiley/rasterx` cover the renderer side but are most
# commonly used by Fyne GUI apps for icon rasterization rather than
# standalone CLI tools.  go-cover-treemap represents the pure-Go SVG-
# generation lane — emit SVG markup directly from typed Go data
# without dragging in librsvg/Cairo or shelling out to a headless
# Chrome.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=234     _mmdr                ← previous round (axis 179 OPENS, 1/0/0)
#   Go=234       ← THIS FILE          (axis 179 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=234  ← next round         (axis 179 CLOSES at triple-234, 1/1/1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_go-cover-treemap() {
    _arguments -s \
        '-coverprofile=[filename of input coverprofile (e.g. cover.out from `go test -coverprofile`)]:coverprofile:_files -g "*.(out|cov|coverage|profile)"' \
        '-w=[width of output in pixels (default 1028)]:pixels:' \
        '-h=[height of output in pixels (default 640)]:pixels:' \
        '-margin-box=[margin between boxes in pixels (default 4)]:pixels:' \
        '-padding-box=[padding between box border and content (default 4)]:pixels:' \
        '-padding=[padding around root content in pixels (default 16)]:pixels:' \
        '-impute-heat[impute heat for parents (weighted sum) and leafs (0.5; default true)]' \
        '-statements[count statements in files for size of files; when false each file is size 1 (default true)]' \
        '-collapse-root[collapse roots that have one child (default true)]' \
        '-only-folders[do not display files; only directories]' \
        '-color-blind[use a color-blind-friendly palette]' \
        '-percent[show percentages in labels]'
}

_go-cover-treemap "$@"
